Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Persian cucumber{1} crosswise into rounds. Trim, peel, and
grate @carrot{3%oz} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Roughly chop
@cilantro{1/4%oz}. Halve @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.
Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince
@ginger{1%thumb}.

== Pickled Veggie Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, carrot, half the cilantro, juice from
half the lime, @sugar{1%tsp}, and as much shallot as you like. (For 4
servings, use juice from whole lime and @sugar{2%tsp}.) Season with a big pinch
of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside to pickle.

== Garlic Potato Wedges ==

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll
use the rest later), a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz} to taste.

== Burgers ==

In a second medium bowl, combine @ground beef{10%oz}, ginger,
@ponzu sauce{18%ml}, remaining cilantro, remaining @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@sugar{1%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. (For 4 servings, use 2 tsp sugar and
1/2 tsp salt.)

Form mixture into two patties (four patties for 4), each slightly wider than a
burger bun.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and
cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

== Assembly ==

While patties cook, halve and toast @potato buns{2}.

> TIP: For a deeper flavor, toast in pan used for patties over medium heat.

Spread as much chili mayo as you like onto cut sides of top buns. Fill buns with
patties and some pickled veggie slaw. Divide burgers between plates; serve with
garlic potato wedges and remaining pickled veggie slaw on the side, with any
remaining chili mayo as a dipper.